Per Chairman Geddes' order to direct these requests to the RAO:

To: Attleboro Public Schools Records Access Officer (RAO)

This is a request for public records under *M.G.L. c. 66, =C2=A7 10* and *9=
50
CMR 32.00*.

*Scope / Date Range (applies to all sections below):* Please produce all
responsive records *from July 1, 2023 through the present*, except the
Financials section (Section 3), which is *FY2022 through the present* as
described below.

*Preferred format & delivery method:* Please provide records
*electronically* (searchable/machine-readable where feasible) and *deliver
via a web portal/link* (or equivalent hosted folder) so the public can
access these materials easily moving forward. If a portal already exists,
please upload there and provide the link. If not, please provide a
shareable link-based delivery method.

*Segregability / redactions:* If any record contains exempt information,
please *redact only the exempt portion* and produce the remainder. The
presence of personally identifying information (PII) should *not* be
treated as a basis to deny the entire record. See *M.G.L. c. 66, =C2=A7 10(=
a)*
(segregable portions) and *Champa v. Weston Public Schools, 473 Mass. 86
(2015)*. For any redaction/withholding, please cite the specific
exemption(s) in *M.G.L. c. 4, =C2=A7 7 cl. 26* and provide a brief explanat=
ion
consistent with *Globe Newspaper Co. v. Police Comm=E2=80=99r of Boston, 41=
9 Mass.
852 (1995)* and *Reinstein v. Police Comm=E2=80=99r of Boston, 378 Mass. 28=
1 (1979)*.
Please produce records on a *rolling basis* as they are located.
------------------------------
SECTION 1 =E2=80=94 Open meetings (ALL): School Committee regular/special m=
eetings,
hearings, and ALL subcommittee meetings (standing/ad hoc)

For *every open meeting* held *July 1, 2023=E2=80=93present*, including:

   - School Committee *regular meetings*
   - School Committee *special meetings*
   - Any *hearings* (including public hearings)
   - *All subcommittee meetings* (standing, ad hoc, working groups, etc.)

Please provide the following *to the extent they exist*:

   1.

   *Recordings*
   - Any *audio and/or video recordings* (including livestream archives;
      recordings hosted by vendors/platforms such as Zoom/Teams/YouTube/cab=
le
      access; and any internally stored files)
   2.

   *Transcripts / captions*
   - Any *written transcripts* (including automated or edited transcripts)
      - Any *closed caption files* (e.g., .vtt/.srt) or caption logs
      - Any platform-generated *meeting text logs* that function as
      transcripts (if maintained)
   3.

   *Minutes*
   - *Draft and approved minutes*, including attendance, votes, and any
      lists of documents/exhibits used or referenced
   4.

   *Notices, agendas, and meeting packets*
   - Meeting notices/postings, agendas, and *all attachments* distributed
      as part of the meeting packet (including revisions)
   5.

   *Documents/exhibits used or presented*
   - All documents and exhibits used, presented, referenced, or distributed
      at the meeting (slides, handouts, policy drafts, marked-up versions,
      reports, memos, spreadsheets, public-facing packets, etc.)
   6.

   *Community engagement records (within any of the above
   meetings/subcommittees/hearings)* Please provide any records the
   district maintains that reflect or capture community engagement or publi=
c
   input, including (to the extent maintained):
   - Public comment sign-in sheets / speaker lists / speaker order lists
      - Written public comments submitted for the record (emails, letters,
      forms, PDFs, etc.) and any compilations of those comments that were
      distributed to members
      - Any =E2=80=9Cpublic comment packets=E2=80=9D or compiled correspond=
ence provided to
      the Committee/subcommittee
      - If remote meetings were used: any *Q&A logs, chat logs, raised-hand
      lists, or public input queues* maintained by the platform or saved by
      the host
      - Any surveys, feedback forms, or community input summaries prepared
      for, presented at, or circulated in connection with a meeting item

(If records are organized by committee/subcommittee name and date, that
organization is fine=E2=80=94please preserve it.)
------------------------------
SECTION 2 =E2=80=94 Executive sessions (records not protected from disclosu=
re /
segregable portions)

For *all executive sessions* held *July 1, 2023=E2=80=93present* (including=
 School
Committee and any subcommittee executive sessions), please provide the
following *to the extent they exist and are not lawfully withheld*:

   1.

   *Executive session minutes* (draft and approved) for any executive
   session for which the purpose for confidentiality has expired, consisten=
t
   with *M.G.L. c. 30A, =C2=A7 22(f)=E2=80=93(g)* (review and release upon =
request).
   2.

   *Documents/exhibits/materials used in executive session* that are no
   longer protected from disclosure because the executive session purpose h=
as
   expired, subject to any applicable Public Records Law exemptions (e.g.,
   attorney-client privilege, privacy, etc.).
   3.

   *Segregable portions* of executive session records after redaction of
   exempt information, rather than withholding in full where partial
   disclosure is possible.

I understand some executive session content may remain non-disclosable if
release would defeat the lawful purpose or is otherwise exempt. I am
requesting that the district (a) conduct the required review, (b) release
what is releasable, and (c) produce redacted/segregable portions rather
than deny in full.
------------------------------
SECTION 3 =E2=80=94 Financials / audits (FY2022=E2=80=93Present)

For *FY2022 through the present*, please provide:

   1.

   The *Annual Comprehensive Financial Report (ACFR)* (or =E2=80=9CCAFR=E2=
=80=9D if titled
   that way for any year) for:
   - FY2022
      - FY2023
      - FY2024
      - FY2025 (if completed/issued)
      - Any newer fiscal year ACFR/CAFR *if issued*
   2.

   *All independent auditor=E2=80=99s reports* associated with those ACFRs/=
CAFRs
   for FY2022 through the most recently issued year.
   3.

   *All management letters, internal control findings, and/or material
   weakness findings* issued by auditors for FY2022 through the most
   recently issued year.
   4.

   Any *Corrective Action Plans (CAPs)* and/or written district responses
   addressing audit findings for FY2022 through the most recently issued ye=
ar.
   5.

   *Current-year / interim financial records (to present)*:
   - Any budget-to-actual reports, interim financial statements, quarterly
      financial reports, cash flow summaries, or other financial status rep=
orts
      routinely provided to leadership/School Committee for the *current
      fiscal year* through the most recent available date.

(If some items are already publicly posted, please provide the link(s) and
also produce any responsive records not posted.)
------------------------------
Fee waiver request

I request a *full waiver of all fees*, because this request is made in the
public interest for broad dissemination and public oversight, not for a
commercial purpose. If you believe any fees are warranted, please provide a
detailed, itemized good-faith estimate and identify what portion (if any)
you are declining to waive and why.

Thank you.

Sincerely,
Joey Ford

